dct_description_sm: One of a series of maps created or annotated by Alfred C. Kinsey, Most contain gall wasp data. Several only contain data on other types of flora and fauna. On this map, data points appear in California, Colorado, Illinois, Minnesota, Montana, Oregon, Utah, Washington, Wisconsin, and Wyoming. Data points also extend into Western Canada. Some data points extend north beyond the printed border of the map. Species are listed in Latin (binomial nomenclature) and color coded (see Caption field).

Caption: Var. tuberculatrix, Var. similis, Var. arefacta, Var. multispinosa, Var. coloradensis, Var. subcoloradesis [sic], Var. tumida, Var. xerophila, Var. wasatchensis, Var. californica, Var. versicolor, Var. melanderi, Var. rubriderma, Var. sierranensis, Var. descansonis, Undescribed Varieties.
Base map type 1 (USGS. Edition of May 1906, reprinted 1922.)
